node.title: Livestream: PM with update on Tonga, COVID-19 vaccine rollout for kids
node.description: The Prime Minister speaks in Auckland.
node.content: ["This livestream is expected to start at 11:50am.\u00a0", "Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern is joined by Defence Minister and Associate Minister of Health Peeni Henare to provide an update on COVID-19 and the emergency situation in Tonga.\u00a0", "Ardern is expected to speak about the deployment of a Royal New Zealand Air Force P-3K Orion to Tonga after the island nation was hit with a tsunami in the wake of a nearby underwater volcanic eruption.\u00a0", "Ardern will also speak about the commencement of paediatric vaccinations for 5-11 year olds. As part of the visit to the T\u0101maki Vaccination Clinic, the Prime Minister will receive her COVID-19 booster shot.\u00a0", "Watch the livestream.\u00a0", "App users watch here.\u00a0"]
